Criminal acts of U.S. CIA
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- The U.S. reshuffled many leading officials and working agents  including the chief and deputy chief of the South Korean branch of the U.S. Central Intelligence Agency (CIA), said the South Korean newspaper Choong-Ang Ilbo on February 1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This is an unprecedented shake-up, the paper said, and continued:   The drastic personnel change was made according to a "measure taken to expand activities of gathering and  analysing information under the changed situation of the Korean peninsula." The reshuffle is characterized by a remarkable increase of experts in north affairs.
   During his Seoul trip at the end of last year, director of the U.S. CIA already informed the authorities of the measure on shake-up and its purpose.      
   The recent shakeup is closely linked with the start of "operation plan 5027" aimed at invading the DPRK.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Needless to say, the U.S., hell-bent on provoking the second Korean War of aggression, carried out the drastic shake up of CIA personnel for the purpose of further intensifying espionage, and subversive and smear activities against the DPRK.
